 The CGView Comparison Tool (CCT) is a package for visually comparing
 bacterial, plasmid, chloroplast, or mitochondrial sequences of interest to
 existing genomes or sequence collections. The comparisons are conducted
 using BLAST, and the BLAST results are presented in the form of graphical
 maps that can also show sequence features, gene and protein names, COG
 category assignments, and sequence composition characteristics. CCT can
 generate maps in a variety of sizes, including 400 Megapixel maps suitable
 for posters. Comparisons can be conducted within a particular species or
 genus, or all available genomes can be used. The entire map creation
