     filename-based bookmark every time one toggles a bm.el one.


Package: elpa-browse-kill-ring
Description-md5: 2c595aaaa4d4730c6f67e3837791cd24
Description-en_GB: interactively insert items from kill-ring
 Ever feel that 'C-y M-y M-y M-y ...' is not a great way of trying to find
 that piece of text you know you killed a while back? Then browse-kill-
 ring.el is for you.
 .
 Note that the command keeps track of the last window displayed to handle
 insertion of chosen text; this might have unexpected consequences if you
 do 'M-x browse-kill-ring', then switch your window configuration, and try
