 GNU Common Lisp (GCL) is a Common Lisp compiler and interpreter
 implemented in C, and complying mostly with the standard set forth in the
 book "Common Lisp, the Language I".  It attempts to strike a useful middle
 ground in performance and portability from its design around C.
 .
 This package contains an emacs interface to GCL.

Package: elpa-geiser
Description-md5: bd2b9ebe1c20149dada06b7858f44898
Description-en_GB: enhanced Scheme interaction mode for Emacs
 Geiser features an enhanced REPL and a set of minor modes improving Emacs' basic scheme major mode. The main functionalities provided are:
