 search and identifiy stars or other point-like sources, do photometry,
 transform/display a FITS image to a popular graphics format, ...) while
 the details of a certain operation are specified via command switches and
 arguments. Therefore this package does not need any higher level operating
 environment than a standard UNIX shell, however, processing the related
 data might require a little more knowledge of the used shell itself. If
 you find this program useful in your research, please cite
 2012MNRAS.421.1825P as "2012, MNRAS, 421, 1825". See also the web page of
 the project, found at http://fitsh.net/. That page gathers information
