 Apophenia builds upon the GNU Scientific and SQLite libraries,
 MySQL/mariaDB is also supported. The core functions are written in C, but
 experience has shown them to be easy to bind in Python, Julia, Perl, Ruby,
 etc. The source code is distributed under the GNU General Public License
 version 2 (GPL2).
